&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part-time job share applicants will be considered&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A 12 months fixed term vacancy or secondment opportunity has arisen for an experienced Senior Medical Secretary to provide a comprehensive secretarial service to 2 full-time Consultant Haematologists as well as secretarial support to the wider Secretarial team within the Trust’s Oncology/ Haematology Directorate. The post holder will also be required to undertake PA duties to the Clinical Director for the Haematology Directorate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you have medical secretarial experience, excellent verbal and written skills, the ability to prioritise and work under pressure as well as a caring and compassionate nature, then we would like to hear from you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essential requirements include the AMSPAR qualification or equivalent, also an RSA level 2 or equivalent typing qualification plus an in depth working knowledge of the Microsoft office package. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal visits or general enquiries, please contact Gaynor Jenkins, Directorate Support Manager on 01905 768914.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
